parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Fuel Odor Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and fuel odor issue can cause a fire hazard, especially when parked in an enclosed space, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell inside and outside the vehicle
fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel droplets appearing below the left-hand fuel tank
malfunction indicator lamp illuminating
fuel smell in the garage
fuel leak when filling up with fuel
fuel vapor valve wet from fuel
strong fuel smell when driving or parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift linkage can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails
the vehicle becomes stuck in drive
the transmission linkage cable breaks
the plastic grommets connecting the shift handle to the transmission break
the vehicle is unable to shift out of park into any gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to dangerous situations, especially in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the pedal is stuck at an approximate 1/2 height up from the floor surface
the pedal throw is minimal
the clutch system works correctly but the pedal is not in its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque tube/flex plate bearings can cause the transmission to freeze/fail, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A rattling noise comes from under the vehicle
a propeller shaft bolt inside the torque tube assembly comes loose and damages the bearing inside the torque tube
the vehicle makes a weird noise and starts to roll on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on or turns on and off intermittently
indicating a problem with the airbag system. The light may come on during acceleration
after restarting the engine
or while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dislodged connectors under the seat can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on or turns on and off intermittently
indicating a problem with the airbag system. The connectors under the seat may be dislodged
causing the system to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An intermittent airbag system failure can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light turns on and off intermittently
indicating a problem with the airbag system. The system may malfunction after driving for a certain period
parking
or restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A melted airbag can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag has melted
indicating a problem with the airbag system.
